text.section:
Except as provided in this section, this subtitle and the other insurance laws of the State do not apply to:
a grand or subordinate lodge or society, order, or association that:
was doing business in the State on December 31, 1963;
provides benefits exclusively through local or subordinate lodges; and
does not issue benefit certificates;
an order, society, or association that:
limits its membership to individuals engaged in one or more crafts or hazardous occupations in the same or similar lines of business; and
insures only its members and their families and dependents; or
as to individual health insurance policies, offers those policies in this State only to members of the Mennonite Church and their dependents and families;
was formed as a fraternal benefit society under the laws of the State of Indiana prior to January 1, 1966 for the purpose of providing mutual aid in affiliation with the Mennonite Church; and
is registered as a foreign corporation under § 7-202 of the Corporations and Associations Article;
a society or auxiliary of an order, society, or association described in item (2) of this subsection;
a domestic society that:
limits its membership to employees of a particular municipal area or a designated firm, business house, or corporation;
provides for individual death benefits not exceeding $400 per year or disability benefits not exceeding $350 per year or both; and
does not issue benefit certificates;
a domestic society or association that:
has a purely religious, charitable, or benevolent purpose;
provides for individual death benefits not exceeding $400 per year or disability benefits not exceeding $350 per year or both;
does not issue benefit certificates; and
has a membership of not more than 1,000 individuals; and
any association, whether or not a fraternal benefit society:
that was organized before 1880;
the members of which are officers or enlisted, regular or reserve, active, retired, or honorably discharged members of the Armed Forces or the Sea Services of the United States; and
a principal purpose of which is to provide insurance and other benefits to its members and the dependents or beneficiaries of its members.
